race.comment: TWILIGHT TALE (8) closed off well in a similar race 21 days ago, finishing 1.8L off the winner when getting out late in the piece. CJP hops back in the saddle today which is a big tick for her chances. Likely to be back in the run but can swoop over the top to return to winning ways. WEMBANYAMA (6) stepped out to 1800m for the first time last start and finished off impressively when looking for the hat-trick. The form out of that race has been solid and the rise in trip doesn't look an issue judging by the way he finished off there. Can get back to winning ways. FIRST ENCOUNTER (2) has gotten a long way back in his past couple when jumping favourite following an impressive first-up effort. He's been left with too much to do but now draws a much softer gate with ZJP claiming 3. Can go a couple better. ROCKING SOCIETY (1) can improve again now third-up off the York Cup. AUTUMN REBEL (5) is another who comes through the York Cup and is not to be discounted.
